# Metric Resource: InformationContent
<https://w3id.org/cq2onto/metric/InformationContent> a dqv:Metric ;

    dcterms:identifier "https://w3id.org/cq2onto/metric/InformationContent" ;
    dcterms:title "Semantic-level comparison using WordNet synsets and IC scores"@en ;
    rdfs:label "InformationContent: Semantic-level comparison using WordNet synsets and IC scores"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "information_content"^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:version "0.0.1"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
    dcat:landingPage <https://w3id.org/cq2onto/metric/InformationContent> ;

    # Descriptive Content
    dcterms:description """
This metric computes a semantic similarity between two labels by mapping each to its WordNet synset and comparing them with an Information-Content-based similarity (Resnik / Lin / Jiang-Conrath), returning a score in [0, 1].

**Calculation Process:**

1. Map both the generated and gold labels to WordNet synsets (best-sense disambiguation).
2. Find the lowest common ancestor (LCA) of the two synsets in the WordNet hierarchy.
3. Compute IC(s) = -log(P(s)) for each synset using a corpus-based probability estimate.
4. Combine via Lin similarity: 2 * IC(LCA) / (IC(s_gen) + IC(s_gold)).
5. Take the maximum similarity across all gold labels.

**Example:**

Generate_Label: Beverage

Gold_Standard_Label: Wine

InformationContent(Generate_Label, Gold_Standard_Label) = 0.74

**What is being measured?**

This metric captures hierarchical semantic distance: pairs of concepts close to each other in the WordNet taxonomy and that share informative ancestors score higher than pairs that only share generic ancestors.
""" ;
    dcat:keyword "Ontology Concept Matching"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Metric"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Classes"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "WordNet"@en ;

    # Relationships and Provenance
    dpv:isApplicableFor <https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q184754> ;
    ftr:hasBenchmark <https://w3id.org/cq2onto/benchmark/ALL> ;
    sio:SIO_000234 <https://w3id.org/cq2onto/metric/InformationContent> ;
    ftr:supportedBy <https://w3id.org/cq2onto/> ;
    dqv:inDimension "Ontology Engineering"^^xsd:string ;

    # Provenance
